Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{0.25%tsp} for the noodles.

Halve any thick @Tenderstem® Broccoli{80%g} stems lengthways, then cut widthways into thirds.

Trim the @Green Beans{80%g}, then cut into thirds. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve the @Lime{1/2}.

When boiling, add the @Egg Noodle Nest{125%g}, green beans and broccoli to the water.

Cook until tender, ~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and run under cold water to stop the noodles sticking together and to keep the veg vibrant.

Meanwhile, boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Pour the @Boiled Water{200%ml} for the sauce into a #measuring jug{}.

Add the @Ketjap Manis{25%g}, @Soy Sauce{15%ml}, @Peanut Butter{30%g} and @Sugar{1%tsp} for the sauce. Stir well.

Pop the #jug{} to one side.

== Stir-Fry ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Drain the @King Prawns{150%g}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw prawns.

Once hot, add the prawns and @Coleslaw Mix{120%g}.

Cook, stirring frequently, until slightly softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in the @Red Thai Style Paste{50%g} and the garlic. Cook, stirring, for ~{1%minute} more.

Add the peanut sauce to the pan and stir well until combined.

Stir through the cooked noodles, green beans and broccoli to coat them in the sauce, then bring to the boil. Simmer until slightly thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Once thickened, remove from the heat. Taste and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

Add a good squeeze of lime juice and a splash of water if you feel it needs it.

== To Serve ==

  Share the prawn noodle stir-fry between your @bowls{2}.

Crush the @Salted Peanuts{25%g} in the unopened sachet using a #rolling pin{}, then sprinkle over the top to finish.

Serve with any remaining lime cut into wedges for squeezing over.

Enjoy!